<p><b>Pulp magazines</b> (or <b>pulp fiction</b>; often referred to as "the pulps") were inexpensive <a href="/wiki/Fiction" title="Fiction">fiction</a> magazines. They were widely published from the 1920s through the 1950s. The term <i>pulp fiction</i> can also refer to mass market <a href="/wiki/Paperback" title="Paperback">paperbacks</a> since the 1950s.</p>
