<p><a href="/wiki/Sinclair_Lewis" title="Sinclair Lewis">Sinclair Lewis</a>, first American winner of the <a href="/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Literature" title="Nobel Prize in Literature">Nobel Prize in Literature</a>, worked as an editor for <i><a href="/wiki/Adventure_(magazine)" title="Adventure (magazine)">Adventure (magazine)</a></i>, writing filler paragraphs (brief facts or amusing anecdotes designed to fill small gaps in page layout), advertising copy, and a few stories.</p>
<p><a name="Publishers" id="Publishers"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Pulp_magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Publishers">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Publishers</span></h2>
